## Quick Start

### 1. Initialize Development Environment

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone <repo-url>
cd dotnet-self-learning-architect

# Run setup script
source scripts/set-env.sh development

# Validate configuration
./scripts/validate-env.sh
# Copy template
cp .env.template .env

2. configure secrets 

# Edit with your values
code .env

# Or use CLI
./scripts/configure-secrets.sh --interactive

3. verify setup 
# Check agent status
dotnet run --project src/Agent.CLI -- status

# Run validatio
dotnet run --project src/Agent.CLI -- validate-env

4Environment Hierarchy
1. Repository Root ( .env.template )
Purpose: Master template with all possible variables
When to edit: Adding new global configuration options
Location: Repository root
Key sections:
 
Azure cloud credentials
 
GitHub integration
 
Model provider API keys
 
Feature flags
2. Source Code ( src/.env.template )
Purpose: Runtime engine configuration
When to edit: Changing agent behavior, timeouts, threading
Location:  src/.env.template 
Key sections:
 
Function execution timeouts
 
Subagent orchestration limits
 
State management (SQLite/Memory/PostgreSQL)
 
Telemetry and observability
3. Project-Specific ( src/Agent.*/.env.* )
Purpose: Component-specific overrides
When to edit: Tuning individual services
Location: Each project directory
Project	File	Purpose	
Agent.Runtime	`.env.runtime`	Core execution engine	
Agent.CLI	`.env.cli`	Interactive command-line tool	
Agent.WebAPI	`.env.web`	ASP.NET Core hosting	
Agent.Tests	`tests/.env.test`	Test isolation	

4. Docker ( docker/.env.* )
Purpose: Container runtime configuration
When to edit: Deploying with Docker Compose
Location:  docker/  directory
File	Purpose	
`.env.docker`	Container agent runtime	
`.env.docker-compose`	Supporting services (Redis, PostgreSQL, monitoring)	

5. Infrastructure ( infra/terraform/.env.terraform )
Purpose: Infrastructure as Code variables
When to edit: Provisioning Azure resources
Location:  infra/terraform/ 
Key sections:
 
Terraform backend configuration
 
Azure resource naming
 
Scaling and SKU settings
 
Network configuration
Core Variables
Required Variables (All Environments)

Variable	Description	Example	
`AGENT_RUNTIME_VERSION`	Semver of agent	`1.0.0`	
`AGENT_ENVIRONMENT`	Deployment target	`Development`, `Staging`, `Production`	
`AZURE_TENANT_ID`	Azure AD tenant GUID	`12345678-...`	
`AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID`	Azure subscription GUID	`87654321-...`	
`AZURE_CLIENT_ID`	Service principal app ID	`abcdef12-...`	
`AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET`	Service principal secret	`***`	
`GITHUB_TOKEN`	GitHub PAT with repo scope	`ghp_...`	
`OPENAI_API_KEY`	For GPT-5.3-Codex	`sk-...`	
`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`	For Claude models	`sk-ant-...`	

Critical Security Variables

Variable	Risk if Exposed	Rotation Frequency	
`AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET`	Cloud resource access	90 days	
`GITHUB_TOKEN`	Repository access	90 days	
`OPENAI_API_KEY`	Model API billing	On compromise	
`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`	Model API billing	On compromise	

